The paper deals with using meta-data from photo-sharing websites to obtain descriptions of geographic locations, which is a task that falls under information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses using machine learning techniques to learn vector space embeddings of geographic locations, which is a task that falls under natural language processing (cs.CL), as well as deep learning (cs.DL) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses using these embeddings to model and predict ecological features, which is a task that falls under social and information networks (cs.SI).
